attributes.magic: PE32 executable (console) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered hacktool. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Change PowerShell Policies to an Insecure Level - PowerShell
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects use of Set-ExecutionPolicy to set insecure policies

crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Felix Bilstein - yara-signator at cocacoding dot com

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a version of the RemCom remote administration tool, often abused by attackers for lateral movement and remote code execution. It installs itself as a service named 'RemComSvc' to provide backdoor access. It uses named pipes like '\\.\\pipe\\RemCom_communicaton', '\\.\\pipe\\RemCom_stdin', and '\\.\\pipe\\RemCom_stdout' to receive commands and redirect the I/O of processes it creates via CreateProcessA.
